\\\\\ Docker Swarm  \\\\\

Docker Swarm is a container orchestration tool used to manage multiple Docker hosts (servers) as a single cluster.
Why we use Swarm?
When applications grow, one server is not enough.
Swarm helps to:
Run containers on multiple servers
Auto-restart failed containers
Scale applications easily
Load balance traffic
High availability
Practical Example
Suppose an e-commerce app has:
Frontend container
Backend container
Database container
If one server crashes, Swarm automatically runs containers on another server.
Main Components
Manager Node → Controls the cluster
Worker Node → Runs containers
Common Commands
docker swarm initdocker node lsdocker service create nginxdocker service scale web=5
Real-Time Usage
Used in:
Production environments
Multi-server applications
High availability setups
Microservices architecture

  \\\\\\Docker Stack \\\\

Docker Stack is used to deploy multiple services together in Docker Swarm using a YAML file.
It works like:
docker-compose → for single server
docker stack → for Swarm cluster
Why we use Stack?
Instead of creating containers one by one, we define everything in one file.

scaleout  - increasing conatiners
scalein - decreasing containers

